body:
I wrote a long comment and then GNOME crashed and when I came back thw whole thread was gone.  :(

I will try to recreate it.

You CAN relax from required to optional, but is it really worth the effort?

If you want to keep ir required, I'll approve it, but I think you should do one or the other of these:

Option 1: Leave it optional.  Declare this struct as an AND.  Accept that an empty struct is semantically valid.  The only downside to this is if you end up needing more than AND, but even that can be handled with sub-structs I think.

Option 2: Define it as a union.  If you need an AND you provide a somewhat duplicative 2nd option, like:

```
// +unionMember
// +optional
TopologyConstraints []TopologyConstraint

// +unionMember
// +optional
TopologyAstrologyConstraints *TopologyAstrologyConstraints

// +unionMember
// +optional
TopologyDayOfWeekConstraints *TopologyDayOfWeekConstraints
```

and

```
type TopologyAstrologyConstraints struct {
  // +optional 
  TopologyConstraints []TopologyConstraint

  // +optional
  RequiredStarSign StarSign
}

type TopologyDayOfWeekConstraints struct {
  // +optional 
  TopologyConstraints []TopologyConstraint

  // +optional
  RequiredDayOfWeek DayOfWeek
```

What I don't want, in the course of evolution, is something like:
* A is mutually exclusive with B
* B is mutually exclusive with A
* C is only valid when B is set
* D is valid when either A or  B is set but not when C

The last thing to think about is who will consume this data and how they will interpret in the face of version skew.  If they don't know about a particular field (they are back-rev vs. API server) will they misinterpret the config in a bad way?  The canonical example of this is NetworkPolicy.  Because of bad decisions, we can't add new criteria because a back-rev implementation will not know the new criteria, and thus NOT INSTALL the intended rules.

Doesn't this need the same tags as PodGroupSpec?

```
	// +k8s:ifDisabled(TopologyAwareWorkloadScheduling)=+k8s:forbidden
	// +k8s:ifEnabled(TopologyAwareWorkloadScheduling)=+k8s:optional
```

DV folks will be working up a new "recipe" for adding a gated field, and while this formulation is a little verbose,  I think it is correct enough.  Maybe we can streamline the tag-expression later.

@aaron-prindle

